      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod-screw interface. Stiffness QoI changed by 1.1% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation estimated discretization error of 0.8% for yield force. GCI < 1.5% for all QoIs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge to <1e-6 relative norm; energy balance checked.",
      "rationale": "Direct sparse solver used for linear steps; Newton-Raphson with line search for nonlinear contact. Residual norms converged to <1e-8. Energy imbalance <0.01%. No spurious hourglassing modes detected. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented modelling protocol with independent peer review of boundary condition and load application setup.",
      "rationale": "A written modelling protocol specifying boundary conditions, load application points, and contact definitions was prepared prior to analysis. An independent senior engineer reviewed the setup against the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry. No use errors identified. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear-elastic isotropic constitutive model appropriate for titanium alloy below yield; contact formulation validated for screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modelled as linear-elastic isotropic (E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) consistent with published material data and the sub-yield loading regime. Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient μ=0.25 used at screw-rod interface, consistent with prior FDA validation studies. Model form uncertainty bounded by ensemble spread. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon tests; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and Poisson ratio derived from ASTM E8 tensile coupon tests on same heat of Ti-6Al-4V bar stock. Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements (n=5 per lot). Torque-preload relationship for set-screw quantified by calibrated torque wrench with ±3% accuracy. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=500). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production lots with documented traceability; samples span at least two independent lots.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from two production lots (Lot A: n=6, Lot B: n=5). All components traceable to device history records. Constructs assembled per IFU torque specification by trained operators. Sample variability characterised; coefficient of variation <4% for stiffness across constructs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate physiological loading environment including at least two load magnitudes or load angles.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standardised load configuration (static compression-bending at 10° offset). Only one test condition evaluated; no variation in load angle or magnitude was explored. This limits the factor to Gradation 2 against the required Gradation 3. Accepted as a documented limitation with compensating validation evidence from the multi-site dataset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to physical test fixture; set-screw torque, fixture compliance, and load application replicated.",
      "rationale": "Physical fixture compliance measured on universal test machine and incorporated into FEA as a spring boundary condition. Set-screw torque mapped to preload via torque-preload calibration. Load application point and offset angle matched to fixture geometry within ±0.5 mm and ±0.2°. Equivalency confirmed by sensitivity analysis. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; all QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and absolute difference <10%.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force (0.2% offset), force at 40 mm displacement. Experimental uncertainty (uexp) characterised from N=11 constructs; simulation uncertainty (usim) from mesh convergence, material variability, and ensemble spread. E/uval: stiffness=0.82, yield force=1.31, force@40mm=1.74. All <1.96. Absolute differences: 3.1%, 6.8%, 8.4%, all <10%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
