    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted on the basis of compensating multi-site experimental evidence and the standardised nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference <10%) are satisfied across all three quantities of interest. The credibility assessment team accepts the FEA model as fit for the stated COU. Note: supplemental third-laboratory evidence was incorporated after package signing without re-signing; the primary decision basis remains the original N=11 two-laboratory dataset.",
